docs.lead_paragraph: AT a conference on the population crisis a few years ago in London, Dr. Alan F. Guttmacher, the tall, bouncy 70-year-old president of Planned Parenthood-World Population, was listening to a speaker decry the soaring birth rate in developing countries.
